==English==

===Etymology 1===
Origin uncertain.  According to the [http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=brat Online Etymology Dictionary], the term "brat" derives from an Old English (Old English) slang term meaning "beggar's child". Originally a northern, Midlands and western England dialect word for "makeshift or ragged garment;" probably the same word as {{etyl|ang|-}} bratt "cloak," which is from a Celtic source (cf. O.Ir. bratt "cloak, cloth").

====Pronunciation====
